 in the high end game.  The pet, much like Wake of Karana, is gravy.  Something to have for the sake of having.  Would it be nice for it be useful? Of course.  Is it essential to our development as a class? No.  Would the repurcussions of Verant making it a miniature familiar be so large and loud that Verant wouldn't even consider it? Yes.  <br><br>We all know wizards would throw a fit.  Every other post for months afterwards on Graffe's would be a call to have Druid's nerfed, or have their familiars made better, because &quot;Wizards are supposed to be the Masters of Familiars!&quot;  <br><br>You'd end up with clerics wanting their hammer to be a familiar and shaman wanting their pet to not only fight, but also give them stat increases.  Monks would start suggesting that Boo Boo means a druid can replace a them as pullers, and warriors would suggest we can taunt better than they can now with our pet.  Mages would probably storm Verant HQ and burn it down for making druid pets better in some way than mage pets.<br><br>Verant isn't going to subject themselves to that to make the single most hated class in the game better off. <p><p><center><img src=http://lilyanaeq.homestead.com/files/Signatures/Aidon.jpg><BR> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24579">Aidon</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubroomhilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broomhilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/22/02 9:49:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26844.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I think the fact that Verant gave us Dire Charm, our regular animal charm spells are good, and they went through the trouble of re-doing animals in